CP Alabi said detectives were immediately dispatched to every nook and crooning of the country to search for the suspect to get to the root of the sudden disappearance of the lady. He added that as the search was ongoing with the partnership with other Security agencies, sadly while the searching was ongoing information got to the police that the lifeless body of the lady was found on a carter bridge, Lagos Island and her body was deposited at the mortuary for an autopsy to be conducted on her. Nigerian Youths Mourn Bamise, The Young Lady Who Was Killed… Man Kills Landlord Over Girl Friends “While the recovery of the girl’s body was on, information came in that the suspect had been arrested by the Department of State Security Services at Ososa -Ijebu where he went to hide in a friend’s house and the friend was also arrested. “The 47-year-old suspect has not made any useful information on why he killed the girl. We condole with the bereaved family and assure them that justice would be served accordingly.” The police boss, however, said no crime would go unpunished in the state.